The migration path is now end-to-end. A **transformation execution engine**
(`@dataferry/transform`) does the heavy lifting, driven by an **agentic
pipeline** — discovery, a coordinator, batch processing, and workers, watched
over by monitor and validator agents. A **dry-run migration preview** and a
migration detail page let you inspect a run before committing, with mappings,
execute, cancel, and template-use all wired to queues. The agent core was also
made **provider-agnostic** via LiteLLM.

